      "role": "user",
      "content": "Okay, I get the physics. But you mentioned blockages being dangerous. In the manual, it talks about how small insects or debris can get stuck inside the tube. Can you give some more specific detail on how those types of blockages specifically affect the pressure reading? Is it a total failure or just a slow drift?",
